sentences: She went on to record her own album in 1973 on MCA/UNI Records.
She recorded with and produced some women's music including Meg & Cris at Carnegie Hall (1983).
She worked as a duo with Cris Williamson throughout the 1990s, producing, engineering and releasing three CDs together.

In the early 1980s, Fure moved to the independent side of the industry discovering the blossoming genre known as Women's Music.
The musical career of Tret Fure has spanned five decades.
Within a year she was performing as guitarist and vocalist for Spencer Davis, touring with him and penning the single for his album "Mousetrap".
